<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-1505</num>
  <heading>Examination authority.</heading>
  <text>The acts of the managing general agent are considered to be the acts of the insurer on whose behalf it is acting. A managing general agent may be examined as if it were the insurer.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-41" type="History" path="§6">Oct. 21, 1993, D.C. Law 10-41, § 6, 40 DCR 6014</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 35-3005.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
